reviews.review_text: A much better recording that the previous sbd I have been waiting so long for this show!  This is one of my favorites of all time.  I had a cassette of this show that wore out years ago and I was looking for a suitable musical replacement.  This is surely it.  The Help/Slip/Frank is the best in this universe.  If you know of a better one, let me know.  I would love to hear it.

I Remember I was there with Karen and Brad, third row.  I had previously heard a cassette recording from a dictation recorder, but this is vastly superior!  Hard to hear on the stream, but there was a guy making an unusually load noise sitting next to Brad.  Boy was he pissed off!  As I recall it was very warm inside the theater and the band was sweating buckets under the lights.  There was also mono-chromatic video support at this show...I think

watch it live Grateful Dead 6-19-76 Capitol Theatre Passaic NJ  
.
Voodoonola2    Voodoonola2·78 videos

In another time's forgotten space Wow! Does this show bring back some faded memories! Overwhelming heat in the old theater, as another commented. I too recall the band dripping under the heat. The newer Dead sound emerging. Europe 72 days long gone. Jerry in superfreak look. The younger crowd in hippie rave mode with swirling light show. Generational torch being passed about the time of this show. Early days for the Dead in their late 70s ascendancy!

Terrific quality recording, amazing year This quality of this recording is excellent. As another reviewer said, spectacular version of Franklin's Tower (preceded by Help-->Slipknot!). The levels of Mickey and Bill are spot on.
